:box:Key Provisions of the Pendleton Act, 1883

• The federal government will administer open, competitive examinations for testing the fitness of applicants for the public service.
• All the offices, places, and employments of the federal government shall be arranged in classes and filled by those graded highest in examinations.
Based on this source, what were the TWO MOST LIKELY purposes of the act?

A.Choice: to increase the authority of the legislature

B.Choice: to ensure the competency of government employees

C.Choice: to increase the authority of the president

D.Choice: to guarantee the financial stability of the government

E.Choice: to reduce the practice of political patronage
